title: For Sale:  1895 Finnish Captured Russian M91 Imperial Tula Dragoon - Rare
postcontent: Very rare antique, only other one I found on gunbroker sold for about $3000 in the completed auctions, but I would say this one is even more unique.. If you search gunbroker-advanced search-completed auctions - you have to have an account to see completed auctions - there's only one other one and it sold for about $3000. This has about 90% bluing. Dragoon marked sights. The buttplate says "27" which could be off of an M28 stock, civil guard, or maybe the 27th Jager battalion. It also has a "1" inscribed under the buttplate. Finnish wartime round finger spliced stock. Nice tiger striping on handguard, arctic birch stock. KAB marked rear sight indicating cossack or Dragoon. It is a bit shorter than a regular M91. This was most likely used in the winter war, Finnish civil war, world war I, and WWII, if not all. It's counter bored, no import mark. I have shot it about 5 times and is a consistent shooter, but still would only buy as a collectible and not something to eat a bunch of lead. This is probably a bring-back since there's no import mark. It has the Finnish army SA mark on the side of the barrel shank, imperial tula crest, tang matches receiver and marked 1895 so this considered antique and requires no FFL to sell, but I will not ship. Only trades I'm iterested are Suomi KP31's, M1 Garrands/Carbins(depending on make & condition), Swedish or German mausers, Swiss K31's, FN49's, Russian SKS's, SVT-40's, Romaian PSL's, other mosins, M1917 revolvers, WWII pistols, - Pretty much anything WWII/WWI and/or slight-postwar military weapons. No sporterized or tacticoolized weapons unless it's something super rare. Can add cash to trade or I can add cash to trade depending what you got.
